# Code Review тАФ `src/`

## 1. Inconsistencies

### 1.1 Duplicate Type Definitions

The domain types `GameSession`, `GameParticipant`, `HostedSession`, and `KnownIdentity` are defined in **two** places:

| Type | Canonical (Hexagonal) | Legacy Duplicate |
|---|---|---|
| `GameSession` / `GameParticipant` / `HostedSession` | [GameSession.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/domain/game-session/GameSession.ts) | [db.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/lib/db.ts) (lines 3-35) |
| `KnownIdentity` | [IKnownIdentityRepository.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/application/ports/IKnownIdentityRepository.ts) (lines 1-6) | [db.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/lib/db.ts) (lines 23-28) |
| `PlayerIdentity` | [PlayerIdentity.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/domain/identity/PlayerIdentity.ts) | [wallet.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/lib/wallet.ts) (lines 7-12) |

> [!WARNING]
> The domain `PlayerIdentity` has an `id` field in the adapter ([SecureWalletAdapter.ts:73](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/infrastructure/identity/SecureWalletAdapter.ts#L73)) but **not** in the domain type. The template in [UserView.vue:227](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/pages/UserView.vue#L227) renders `{{ identity.id }}` тАФ this only works because the adapter sneaks in an extra field not declared on the type. This is a type-safety gap.

---

### 1.2 Wrong Import Path for `KnownIdentity`

[UserView.vue:12](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/pages/UserView.vue#L12):
```typescript
import type { KnownIdentity } from '../domain/identity/IKnownIdentityRepository'
```
There is no file at `domain/identity/IKnownIdentityRepository`. The actual file is at `application/ports/IKnownIdentityRepository.ts`. This either relies on path aliasing or will fail at compile time.

---

### 1.3 Router Guard Checks `requiresSession` but Routes Use `requiresAuth`

[identityGuard.ts:21](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/router/guards/identityGuard.ts#L21) checks for `to.meta.requiresSession`:
```typescript
if (!to.meta.requiresSession) {
    return next();
}
```
But most routes in [router/index.ts](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/router/index.ts#L18) only set `requiresAuth: true`. Only the `board` route (line 36) sets `requiresSession: true`. This means the guard **does nothing** for `/games`, `/profile`, and `/games/:gameId` тАФ they have no session-gating despite being behind `requiresAuth`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Either the guard should check `requiresAuth`, or the meta keys should be unified. Currently users without an identity can navigate to `/games` and `/profile` freely.

---

### 1.4 `inject()` Called Inside `onMounted` (Invalid Lifecycle)

[IndexView.vue:12](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/pages/IndexView.vue#L12):
```typescript
onMounted(async () => {
    const identityRepo = inject(Keys.IdentityRepoKey)!  // тЖР BAD
    const id = await identityRepo.getIdentity()
    if (id) { router.replace('/games') }
})
```
Vue's `inject()` **must** be called synchronously during `setup()`, not inside lifecycle hooks. This will silently return `undefined` and the non-null assertion will throw at runtime.

