### 1.6 `ISignalingPort` vs Legacy `SignalingService` API Mismatch

The `ISignalingPort` interface has no `updateBoardId()` method, but the legacy `SignalingService` class does. The `AwsSignalingAdapter` also does not expose `peerName` on `hostOffer`/`boardId` on `guestAnswer` тАФ while the legacy `SignalingService` does. If any MFE code references the legacy service, there'll be behavioral drift.

---

### 1.7 `isKnownIdentity` Duplicated Across Composables

The exact same function exists in both:
- [useSessionActions.ts:45-48](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/composables/useSessionActions.ts#L45-L48)
- [useSignaling.ts:52-55](file:///home/dparadiz/Projects/mykoboard.github.io/src/composables/useSignaling.ts#L52-L55)

Both are identical: query all known identities and `.some(тАж)` match. `useGameSession.ts` returns the one from `useSessionActions`, and the `useSignaling` one is separately wired through the return value. Consolidate into one.

